Quickly.

1193
01:21:44,680 --> 01:21:48,229
So quickly.
I think I'll just go away for a while.

1194
01:21:49,240 --> 01:21:50,195
Where?

1195
01:21:50,320 --> 01:21:53,232
I thought maybe I'd go see my dad.

1196
01:21:54,760 --> 01:21:58,150
I got a better idea.
Let's get married.

1197
01:21:58,280 --> 01:22:00,111
Are you crazy?

1198
01:22:02,160 --> 01:22:04,116
I have been.

1199
01:22:04,880 --> 01:22:06,916
But I love you.

1200
01:22:08,000 --> 01:22:10,514
I can't think about this now.

1201
01:22:10,640 --> 01:22:13,791
Who says you got to think
about everything all the time?

1202
01:22:22,960 --> 01:22:24,916
Billie!

1203
01:22:31,080 --> 01:22:32,911
Billie!

1204
01:22:35,360 --> 01:22:36,952
There.

1205
01:22:37,080 --> 01:22:40,038
Billie, marry me?

1206
01:22:40,320 --> 01:22:42,231
Give me those papers.

1207
01:22:42,360 --> 01:22:44,191
I can't.

1208
01:22:45,840 --> 01:22:47,876
Go, quick. He'll kill you!

1209
01:22:50,400 --> 01:22:52,595
Oh, hello. I didn't hear you.

1210
01:22:52,720 --> 01:22:56,918
- Where have you been?
- What's the matter? Did you miss me?

1211
01:23:02,960 --> 01:23:07,397
I had an idea. You know me,
I hate waiting when I got an idea.

1212
01:23:08,680 --> 01:23:11,148
I don't blame you for being mad.

1213
01:23:11,280 --> 01:23:14,352
I was thinking about
why you're so on edge.

1214
01:23:14,480 --> 01:23:19,235
And then I realised that you don't know
what you mean to me.

1215
01:23:19,360 --> 01:23:21,999
I can feel how much I mean to you,
Harry.

1216
01:23:23,160 --> 01:23:25,833
Hey, I've done a lot
of good things, too.

1217
01:23:25,960 --> 01:23:29,509
Don't forget about those
just cos of one mistake. Here...

1218
01:23:29,640 --> 01:23:31,596
Maybe this'll help.

1219
01:23:32,480 --> 01:23:33,435
Da!

1220
01:23:36,480 --> 01:23:40,359
- Boy, when it rains, it pours!
- Yeah!

1221
01:23:40,480 --> 01:23:42,311
Just name the date.

1222
01:23:43,760 --> 01:23:46,035
I'm thinking of the thirteenth.

1223
01:23:46,160 --> 01:23:47,513
What month?

1224
01:23:47,640 --> 01:23:51,713
It's not a day, it's the Thirteenth
Amendment. No more slavery.

1225
01:23:51,840 --> 01:23:55,355
- What's that supposed to mean?
- I can't marry you, Harry.

1226
01:23:56,440 --> 01:23:57,998
You're too dumb.

1227
01:24:00,080 --> 01:24:03,277
You think dumb people
make this much money?

1228
01:24:03,400 --> 01:24:07,552
I think only a dumb person
would think money makes him smart.

1229
01:24:07,680 --> 01:24:10,638
I got a different kind of life in mind.

1230
01:24:13,960 --> 01:24:16,918
Is this something
your little teacher taught you?

1231
01:24:17,040 --> 01:24:19,110
He's what needs to be different
around here.

1232
01:24:19,240 --> 01:24:22,516
- I don't want you seeing him no more.
- I won't.

1233
01:24:22,640 --> 01:24:26,474
- That's more like it.
- It's not because of you!

1234
01:24:29,080 --> 01:24:31,514
Look, you're upset about the hit,
I know.

1235
01:24:32,560 --> 01:24:36,473
- I'm sorry.
- Let me tell you about that hit.

1236
01:24:36,600 --> 01:24:40,479
Everything I've been reading about and
Paul's been telling me, it mixed me up.

1237
01:24:40,600 --> 01:24:45,720
But when you hit me, everything
fell together and made sense.

1238
01:24:45,840 --> 01:24:49,071
Some people are always giving it
and some are always taking it.

1239
01:24:49,200 --> 01:24:52,397
I'm not taking it any more!

1240
01:24:52,520 --> 01:24:55,990
Why don't we go to my room
and I'll calm you down?

1241
01:24:56,120 --> 01:24:57,951
Marry me or you'll be sorry!

1242
01:24:58,080 --> 01:25:00,958
I'm already sorry. That's why I'm leaving!

1243
01:25:01,080 --> 01:25:04,231
Billie, I'm offering to make you
a real partner.

1244
01:25:04,360 --> 01:25:06,316
Partner in here.

1245
01:25:12,640 --> 01:25:15,200
I want you to be my wife.

1246
01:25:15,320 --> 01:25:18,118
Men are unbelievable.

1247
01:25:18,840 --> 01:25:22,071
I give and give and give
and it's like wallpaper to you.

1248
01:25:22,200 --> 01:25:24,156
You just walk right past it.

1249
01:25:24,280 --> 01:25:27,158
Then you make one effort
and you think we're equal.

1250
01:25:27,280 --> 01:25:31,751
It only looks like a big effort
because you never made one before.

1251
01:25:32,640 --> 01:25:33,595
No!

1252
01:25:37,080 --> 01:25:39,992
Fine.

1253
01:25:43,360 --> 01:25:45,351
We'll see how you get along without me.

1254
01:25:46,360 --> 01:25:49,238
You don't look like you did
five years ago.

1255
01:25:49,360 --> 01:25:50,952
You look like shit!

1256
01:25:52,120 --> 01:25:55,590
Yeah? Well, as far as I'm concerned,
vice versa!

1257
01:25:58,960 --> 01:26:01,599
I'd forgotten how great this really is.

1258
01:26:02,400 --> 01:26:06,029
She's leaving me.
Let's make sure everything's in order.

1259
01:26:06,160 --> 01:26:09,948
Got to get these companies
back in my name.

1260
01:26:20,240 --> 01:26:22,515
Looking for the stuff
I'm always signing?

1261
01:26:22,640 --> 01:26:24,312
Yes.

1262
01:26:24,440 --> 01:26:25,919
Like that file?

1263
01:26:26,040 --> 01:26:27,029
Yes.

1264
01:26:27,160 --> 01:26:29,674
- In the blue cover?
- Yes! Yes!

1265
01:26:31,760 --> 01:26:33,796
- Paul has it.
- What?

1266
01:26:33,920 --> 01:26:36,434
You gave it to him? Why?

1267
01:26:36,560 --> 01:26:39,028
So he could take 'em to the paper.

1268
01:26:40,520 --> 01:26:43,830
- Are you selling me out?
- Hello? Anybody home?

1269
01:26:50,320 --> 01:26:52,276
JJ, lock the doors.

1270
01:26:53,600 --> 01:26:55,830
Get in here and sit down.

1271
01:26:55,960 --> 01:26:59,430
Why, thank you, I'd love a seat!
My feet are killing me.

1272
01:27:03,360 --> 01:27:05,191
Hello!

1273
01:27:05,320 --> 01:27:09,199
- How have you been?
- Very good, thank you. And you?

1274
01:27:09,320 --> 01:27:11,231
Pretty good. Busy.

1275
01:27:11,360 --> 01:27:14,033
Can the tea party crap!
Is she tellin' the truth?

1276
01:27:14,160 --> 01:27:17,436
- Did you take that stuff to the papers?
- Billie always tells the truth.

1277
01:27:17,560 --> 01:27:20,597
All right, pal.
You bring those papers back here.

1278
01:27:20,720 --> 01:27:22,676
Or I will make you very sorry.

1279
01:27:22,800 --> 01:27:24,279
Tell him I'm not bluffing.

1280
01:27:24,400 --> 01:27:25,958
He's not bluffing.

1281
01:27:26,080 --> 01:27:30,392
This would be good for the article.
Six years ago, there was a strike at...

1282
01:27:30,520 --> 01:27:33,159
Shut up! You don't know nothin' about that!

1283
01:27:33,280 --> 01:27:35,316
I know that was a double negative!

1284
01:27:35,440 --> 01:27:36,759
You stupid, goddamn...

1285
01:27:37,680 --> 01:27:40,752
I also happen to know
you've been paying people off,

1286
01:27:40,880 --> 01:27:43,235
so that they won't shut down that base.

1287
01:27:43,360 --> 01:27:44,429
What?

1288
01:27:44,560 --> 01:27:48,792
I forgot, you're not a book reader
like us. You bribed 'em!

1289
01:27:48,920 --> 01:27:50,319
No, no, Billie.

1290
01:27:50,440 --> 01:27:52,715
Bribe is a strong word.

1291
01:27:52,840 --> 01:27:55,559
They got $150,000 each.

1292
01:27:55,680 --> 01:27:58,319
What would you call that? A tip?

1293
01:27:58,440 --> 01:28:01,910
You had no right
to take those papers.

1294
01:28:02,200 --> 01:28:03,952
You had no right to do what you did.

1295
01:28:04,080 --> 01:28:08,119
But you did it. And now that you've done
it, the people have a right to know.

1296
01:28:08,240 --> 01:28:10,231
- What people?
- The people.

1297
01:28:10,360 --> 01:28:11,952
- Never heard of 'em.
- You will.

1298
01:28:12,080 --> 01:28:14,435
12 of them are going to be deciding
where you're going to live.

1299
01:28:14,560 --> 01:28:18,712
- Who are you, the government?
- As a matter of fact, I am.

1300
01:28:18,840 --> 01:28:19,750
Since when?

1301
01:28:19,880 --> 01:28:22,952
Since 1776.

1302
01:28:23,080 --> 01:28:24,308
Exactly.

1303
01:28:26,120 --> 01:28:27,951
All right.

1304
01:28:28,080 --> 01:28:30,640
What'll it take, Paul?

1305
01:28:30,880 --> 01:28:32,552
What do you mean?

1306
01:28:32,680 --> 01:28:36,036
I think he's trying to tip you.

1307
01:28:38,000 --> 01:28:39,638
What'll you take?

1308
01:28:39,760 --> 01:28:43,594
I'll take a beer.
A light one, if you've got it.

1309
01:28:44,600 --> 01:28:46,477
Get back here. Don't try to get funny.

1310
01:28:46,600 --> 01:28:49,717
I ain't never met a guy yet
that didn't have his price.

1311
01:28:49,840 --> 01:28:52,115
I'm ready to talk big numbers.

1312
01:28:52,240 --> 01:28:57,189
You and your big numbers! You'll be
wearing big numbers across your chest.

1313
01:28:57,320 --> 01:29:01,518
There are some things
more important than money.

1314
01:29:01,640 --> 01:29:04,074
Like what? Your career?

1315
01:29:05,960 --> 01:29:07,996
Nope.

1316
01:29:08,120 --> 01:29:10,350
Like doing the right thing.

1317
01:29:17,120 --> 01:29:19,873
Come on, Billie. Let's go.

1318
01:29:25,840 --> 01:29:29,310
Stop it! Stop, Harry!

1319
01:29:30,760 --> 01:29:33,991
- You could've killed him!
- What do you care?!

1320
01:29:34,120 --> 01:29:36,588
I'm gonna marry him, that's what I care!

1321
01:29:36,720 --> 01:29:39,518
- You what?
- You what?

1322
01:29:39,640 --> 01:29:44,077
I'm gonna marry him,
cos he finally smartened up.

1323
01:29:48,360 --> 01:29:50,749
I need a drink.

1324
01:29:50,880 --> 01:29:52,836
Let me get it for you, Mr Devery.

1325
01:29:59,480 --> 01:30:03,712
Am I in the room?
Hello! Am I in the room?

1326
01:30:05,080 --> 01:30:07,310
You been cheatin' on me with this guy?

1327
01:30:07,440 --> 01:30:09,590
No, we never did anything.

1328
01:30:09,720 --> 01:30:12,393
I wanted to, but he wouldn't let me.

1329
01:30:14,120 --> 01:30:15,792
Let's just drop the whole thing.

1330
01:30:15,920 --> 01:30:19,276
You get her, and you don't have to
worry about what I'm doing.

1331
01:30:19,400 --> 01:30:21,311
Oh, but I do worry, Harry.

1332
01:30:21,440 --> 01:30:24,876
See, we got this beautiful
piece of machinery...

1333
01:30:25,000 --> 01:30:27,958
I don't have to listen to you.
You talk more than a senator.

1334
01:30:28,080 --> 01:30:30,275
You wanna screw
Brock Village? Go ahead!

1335
01:30:30,400 --> 01:30:33,119
I got plenty other businesses!
So get out!

1336
01:30:33,240 --> 01:30:34,878
I'm sick of the sight of both of you!

1337
01:30:35,000 --> 01:30:37,833
Your other businesses belong to me.

1338
01:30:37,960 --> 01:30:39,916
Oh, Christ!

1339
01:30:43,080 --> 01:30:47,631
Remember how you used to say we'd
go away, buy a house on the beach?

1340
01:30:47,760 --> 01:30:49,637
Why didn't we ever do that?

1341
01:30:49,760 --> 01:30:51,990
I couldn't do that. I had to work.

1342
01:30:52,120 --> 01:30:54,918
But why? You had five companies
when I met you.

1343
01:30:55,040 --> 01:30:57,918
When was it going to be enough
so we could we enjoy it?

1344
01:30:58,040 --> 01:31:03,512
One thing I have had enough of
is you and Professor Windbag!

1345
01:31:03,640 --> 01:31:07,838
That will be corrected shortly,
when I leave.

1346
01:31:08,720 --> 01:31:12,190
I'll give the companies back to you,
but only one at a time.

1347
01:31:12,320 --> 01:31:14,709
- What?
- And only one a year.

1348
01:31:14,840 --> 01:31:17,559
- What?
- Oh, my God!

1349
01:31:17,680 --> 01:31:20,148
You're calling those senators
and getting that money back.

1350
01:31:20,280 --> 01:31:23,431
Then you're getting out of town
or Paul will write that story.

1351
01:31:24,800 --> 01:31:28,918
If I take their money back,
they close the base, I lose the mall!

1352
01:31:29,040 --> 01:31:31,679
What am I supposed to do?

1353
01:31:31,800 --> 01:31:34,473
- Maybe take a watercolour class?
- Very funny.

1354
01:31:34,600 --> 01:31:35,999
Also, you should walk the beach.

1355
01:31:36,120 --> 01:31:38,998
- I don't live near a beach.
- I'm rich for a little bit.

1356
01:31:39,120 --> 01:31:41,759
I'll buy you a beach
and I'll pay for your watercolour class.

1357
01:31:41,880 --> 01:31:45,793
And I'll get you a ticket to the museum,
so you can see that Van Gogh.

1358
01:31:45,920 --> 01:31:49,629
Are you nuts?
Why should I do all this stuff?

1359
01:31:49,760 --> 01:31:52,513
- You have to ask why?
- Yeah!

1360
01:31:52,640 --> 01:31:56,269
That's why! So you'll know
what all that stuff is for!

1361
01:31:56,400 --> 01:31:59,472
Then maybe you'll find a little bit
of what I've found.

1362
01:32:01,280 --> 01:32:04,795
Trust me, Harry.
This will make you happy.

1363
01:32:04,920 --> 01:32:07,992
How would you know?

1364
01:32:08,120 --> 01:32:11,078
Do you think I was born yesterday?

1365
01:32:11,200 --> 01:32:13,794
God, I love this woman.

1366
01:32:19,840 --> 01:32:21,796
Bye, JJ.

1367
01:32:21,960 --> 01:32:23,916
Bye.

1368
01:32:24,360 --> 01:32:26,191
You ready?

1369
01:32:26,320 --> 01:32:28,276
Absolutely.

1370
01:32:31,880 --> 01:32:34,474
You do what I'm tellin' ya!

1371
01:32:50,000 --> 01:32:55,000
Eng subs ripped by
